# schema-version check (older DB): setting the schema_version metadata to a
# value less than the binary's current version triggers an error. Unlike the
# newer-DB case, SkipsAll does not fire — column-data-validity and its
# dependents still run on a best-effort basis. Exits 2.

np-init SVOLD

np-seed-sql 'UPDATE metadata SET value = ''1'' WHERE key = ''schema_version'''

! exec np admin doctor
stdout 'Schema version'
stdout 'schema is at v1'
stdout 'np admin upgrade'

-- CLAUDE.md --
Use np to manage issues. Run `np agent prime` for setup.
